The following are major news items in leading Japanese newspapers
Friday. Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai: -- Former Japanese
Prime Minister Morihito Hosokawa, saying he had fulfilled his political
responsibility, announced his resignation as a member of the House of
Representative Thursday. Yomiuri, Mainichi: -- The Group of Seven
industrialized countries and Russia will clarify the macroeconomic
policy goals of each country and region in a declaration to be adopted
at their upcoming summit meeting in Birmingham, Britain. Asahi: --
Trade ministers from Canada, the European Union (EU), Japan and the
United States ended a two-day meeting in Versailles, France, Thursday
after adopting a statement for a new approach to promoting global trade
liberalization. Yomiuri, Nihon Keizai: -- The U.S. economy expanded by
an annualized 4.2 percent in the first quarter, accelerating from a 3.7
percent gain in the pervious quarter on stronger consumption.
